Citation.sAbstract: Density, kinematic viscosity, surface tension, and speed of sound of tetradecyl and octadecyl trimethyl ammonium bromide aqueous solutions have been determined. The influence of each surfactant concentration upon these physical properties has also been studied at 298 K. The experimental values of these physical properties have been employed to determine the critical micellar concentration for each surfactant, as well as to analyze the effect of chain length upon this characteristic parameter.
Citation.sTitle: Density, Kinematic Viscosity, Speed of Sound, and Surface Tension of Tetradecyl and Octadecyl Trimethyl Ammonium Bromide Aqueous Solutions
